cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.EC, cs.DS 

This paper deals with prediction markets, which are a type of mechanism design problem in which traders make bets on the outcome of future events. This falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as well as machine learning (cs.LG) and econometrics (cs.EC). The paper also involves numerical simulations, which could fall under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
